-- Item Sorting Program for ComputerCraft

-- Error handler function to print error details
function errorHandler(err)
  print("An error occurred: " .. tostring(err))
  print(debug.traceback())
end

-- Main function to run the sorting program
function main()
  -- Initialization self-check
  if not networkSelfCheck() then
    error("Error: No devices found on the network.")
  end

  local intakeChest = findIntakeChest()
  local storageController = findStorageController()
  local modChests = scanChests()

  if not intakeChest then
    print("Warning: Intake chest not found. Skipping intake chest check for now.")
  else
    print("Intake chest found.")
  end

  if not storageController then
    print("Warning: Storage controller not found. Skipping storage controller check for now.")
  else
    print("Storage controller found.")
  end

  validateModChests(modChests)

  -- Test loop to verify functionality without actual item transfer
  print("Starting test loop...")
  for i = 1, 5 do
    local item = getItemFromIntake(intakeChest)
    if item then
      print("Item found in intake chest: " .. tostring(item))
      if not storeInLimitedStorage(storageController, item) then
        local mod = getItemMod(item)
        local targetChest = findModChest(modChests, mod)
        if targetChest then
          print("Storing item in mod-specific chest: " .. tostring(targetChest))
        else
          print("Storing item in 'other' chest.")
        end
      else
        print("Item stored in limited storage.")
      end
    else
      print("No item found in intake chest.")
    end
  end
end

-- Network self-check to get a list of devices on the network
function networkSelfCheck()
  local devices = peripheral.getNames()
  if #devices == 0 then
    return false
  end
  return true
end

-- Find the intake chest with a Minecraft paper inside
function findIntakeChest()

  print("Mock: Finding intake chest...")
  return "intakeChest"
end

-- Find the sophisticated storage controller or storage_io
function findStorageController()
  -- Mocked function for testing
  print("Mock: Finding storage controller...")
  return "storageController"
end

-- Scan all chests to create a map of mods assigned to chests
function scanChests()
  -- Mocked function for testing
  print("Mock: Scanning chests...")
  return { mod1 = "chest1", mod2 = "chest2" }
end

-- Validate the mod chests to ensure no duplicate mods exist
function validateModChests(modChests)

  print("Mock: Validating mod chests...")
end

-- Get an item from the intake chest
function getItemFromIntake(intakeChest)

  print("Mock: Getting item from intake chest...")
  return "testItem"
end

-- Store the item in limited storage first, if possible
function storeInLimitedStorage(storageController, item)
  -- Mocked function for testing
  print("Mock: Attempting to store item in limited storage...")
  return false
end

-- Find the chest assigned to a specific mod
function findModChest(modChests, mod)
  -- Mocked function for testing
  print("Mock: Finding chest for mod " .. tostring(mod) .. "...")
  return modChests[mod]
end

-- Store the item in the appropriate chest for its mod
function storeInChest(chest, item)
  -- Mocked function for testing
  print("Mock: Storing item in chest " .. tostring(chest) .. "...")
end

-- Store the item in one of the "other" chests
function storeInOtherChest(modChests, item)
  -- Mocked function for testing
  print("Mock: Storing item in 'other' chest...")
end

-- Run the program with global error catching
